oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SOME PROPERTIES OF SWELL IN THE SOUTHERN OCEAN
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hinwood, John B.
Blackman, Deane R.
Lleonart, Geoffrey T.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: swell
Southern Ocean
swell properties
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Records of pressure from a bottom-resident instrument deployed near the western margin of Bass Strait have been analysed. Discrete wind-sea and swell spectra have been identified and have been related to meteorological events. The spectra fit a finite-depth form of the Wallops spectrum.
